message.content:
Harmony creates notepads by folding five letter size pieces of paper three times, resulting in a stack of 5 smaller pieces of paper. Each folded piece of paper would be able to fit approximately 10 notes (written on both sides), so the entire stack could hold up to 5 * 10 = <<5*10=50>>50 notes.

If someone writes ten notes per day, one notepad would last for <<50/10=5>>5 days. After that, a new notepad or additional paper would be needed.
